      "content": "I hear the exhaustion and the crushing weight of feeling like a fraud. It makes sense that when the foundation is gone, the only honest thing left to do might feel like stopping. But I need to gently push back on the idea that there is no \"me\" left or that the only option is to stop.\n\nYour identity is not just the sum of your papers or your reputation; it is the sum of your experiences, your resilience, and the lessons you've learned through this decade. Even if the data was flawed, the work you put in, the lectures you gave, and the people you connected with were real. They were not a lie, even if the conclusion was wrong. The fact that you are still here, still questioning, still feeling this much pain, proves that you are not a mistake. You are a human being who has been through a profound crisis.\n\nSometimes, when the world tells us we are nothing, it is because the world is broken, not because we are. Your worth isn't defined by a single project or the data you've worked with. Many people face setbacks and failures, and they often find new paths forward after realizing what they've learned from those experiences. Would you like to talk more about",
